    <item>
      <title>Explainable AI for Autonomous Driving</title>
      <link>https://sabyasachis.github.io/talk/xai4ad/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 10 May 2021 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://sabyasachis.github.io/talk/xai4ad/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this talk, we review various explainability models that can be applied to interpret pre-trained models and see how they can leveraged for autonomous driving systems.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Review of Image to Image Translation - Methods and Applications</title>
      <link>https://sabyasachis.github.io/talk/i2i-review/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Mar 2021 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://sabyasachis.github.io/talk/i2i-review/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In this talk, I review Image to Image Translation. First, we go over different types of image to image translation. Next, we look at following popular image to image translation methods: pix2pix, GauGAN, CycleGAN, UNIT, MUNIT, and StarGAN. Finally, we look at various applications of image to image translation that are relevant to autonomous driving.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
